Package org.anchoranalysis.feature.calculate.cache

Classes to cache feature-results or parts of feature-results that occur repeatedly among features or across calculations of the same feature.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CacheCreator  
    CalculateForChild<T extends FeatureInput>
    Performs calculations using child-caches instead of the main cache
    CalculationResolver<T extends FeatureInput>
    Searches a cache to reuses a FeatureCalculation if it already exists.
    FeatureSessionCache<T extends FeatureInput>
    A context in which to calculate features while caching certain duplicated internal calculations among the features.
    FeatureSessionCalculator<T extends FeatureInput>
    Calculates features in the context of a particular feature-session.
    FeatureSymbolCalculator<T extends FeatureInput>
    Resolves and calculates a feature by a symbol (an ID/variable-name referring to another feature)
    ResettableCalculation
    A calculation that be invalidated (resetted), removing any existing cached value.
    SessionInput<T extends FeatureInput>
    Encapsulates a feature-input in the context of a particular session.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChildCacheName
    A unique identifier for a child-cache name, that uses a class and optionally additionally a part-name a class: guaranteed to be unique for the class an optional part-name (string): a further division of the class into different caches
    ResolvedCalculation<S,​T extends FeatureInput>
    Like a FeatureCalculation but has been resolved against a cache to reuse any existing identical instance.
    ResolvedCalculationMap<S,​T extends FeatureInput,​U>
    A FeatureCalculationMap that has been resolved against a cache.
